cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper focuses on how to solve PJ puzzles in the cyberspace by a group of physically distributed human players, which involves human-computer interaction. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The approach proposed in the paper involves using stigmergy-inspired Internet-based human collective intelligence, which can be considered as a form of artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the use of technology (Internet-based human collective intelligence) to facilitate human collaboration in solving PJ puzzles, which can be seen as a topic related to computers and society. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The approach proposed in the paper involves integrating the results of all players' exploration in real time through a collective opinion graph, which can be seen as a form of social and information network. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - PJ puzzle can be considered as a game, and the paper proposes an approach to solve it by a group of players, which can be seen as a topic related to game theory.
